    <briefdescription>
<para>Relative clock for all of <ref refid="namespaceILLIXR" kindref="compound">ILLIXR</ref>. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>Please use this instead of std::chrono clocks; this way, you can fake real time without changing your code.</para>
<para>It also eliminates the class of bugs relating to using absolute time instead of time-since-start.</para>
<para>Unfortunately this can&apos;t satisfy <ulink url="https://en.cppreference.com/w/cpp/named_req/Clock">Clock</ulink> because it needs to have data (namely _m_start) shared across link-time boundaries. There&apos;s no clean way to do this with static variables, so instead I use instance variables and Phonebook. </para>
    </detaileddescription>
